post_text:
With remote learning our goal is to provide an optimal learning experience which also keeps our students in the fold of the Dennis Township school community. 100% remote students remain enrolled in a homeroom. 3 days a week they will receive the same exact instruction as the students who are hybrid.
It looks like this:

Day One:
Remote and Hybrid students meet with the homeroom teacher online. (Typically, Wednesdays

Days Two & Three:
Remote and Hybrid students will complete assignments independently. This will include some recorded lessons by the classroom teachers. This work will be posted on the e-learning pages. More information about this will be forth coming to staff next week.

Days Four & Five:
Hybrid students will learn in-person at school. Remote students will be online with a Dennis Township teacher.

We feel this model will keep all students learning the same material at the same pace. This will allow remote students to return to us fully prepared to begin in-person learning with their peers.

post_text: Movie Night - Student Government’s annual outside movie night was another success! Students set up blankets (and sleeping bags and onesies) under the stars and snacked on homemade popcorn, hot chocolate, and movie-theater candy as they watched The Haunting in Connecticut on a new, hand-made screen courtesy of Mr. McGroarty and Mr. Schwartz. 6th grade students made jar lanterns that lit the courtyard and added to the eerie mood. Thanks to all who made this night a success! #dtschoolsrock http://edl.io/n1103138
